MISSION
  Assign a standing mission to ships, planes, or land units.

SYNTAX
  mission <unit-spec> <mission-type> [radius]
  miss    <unit-spec> <mission-type> [radius]

DESCRIPTION
  Sets a unit to automatically perform a mission each update or when
  triggered, without requiring manual commands each time.

  Mission types:
    i  interdiction   - attack enemy units passing through the area
    s  support        - provide fire support to allies attacking nearby
    o  offense        - air support for ground attacks in radius
    e  escort         - escort friendly planes on missions
    r  reserve        - ground reserve (reinforce attacks)
    0  clear          - remove assigned mission

  [radius]  - how far from the unit's location the mission applies

  Units on mission still require fuel/ammunition.  Check with
  'show' to see mission capabilities per unit type.

EXAMPLE
  mission 0 i 3             ship 0 interdict enemies within 3 sectors
  mission * s 5             all planes on support mission, radius 5
  mission 0 0               clear mission from unit 0

SEE ALSO
